article.headline: Harvard sweeps Brown, improves to 8-1 in Ivy
article.linkText: Harvard sweeps Brown, improves to 8-1 in Ivy
article.story: BOSTON -- Corbin Miller scored 14 points and Keith Wright tallied a double-double to help Harvard complete the regular-season sweep over Brown with a 69-42 win on Friday night, keeping the Crimson in first place in the Ivy League. Wright had 12 points and 10 rebounds for Harvard (22-3, 8-1), which used a 22-2 run in the first half to put this one out of reach early and solidify its standing atop the conference. The Crimson have now won 10 of their last 11 games. Harvard led by 21 points at the break and outscored the Bears 32-26 in the second half to seal this contest. The Crimson outrebounded the Bears 40-23 and blocked 10 Brown shots on the night. Sean McGonagill and Matt Sullivan had 11 points apiece to pace Brown (7-19, 1-8), which has lost six straight games beginning with a 68-59 defeat versus Harvard on Jan. 28.
